<item>
            <title>[LU-4864] sanity-hsm needs to clean up the shared_dir created</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4864</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; n in $(seq $AGTCOUNT); &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
                eval export AGTDEV$n=\$\{AGTDEV$n:-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$SHARED_DIRECTORY/arc$n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;\}
                agent=CLIENT$((n + 1))
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; [[ -z &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;${!agent}&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ]]; then
                        [[ $CLIENTCOUNT -eq 1 ]] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; agent=CLIENT1 ||
                                agent=CLIENT2
                fi
                eval export agt${n}_HOST=\$\{agt${n}_HOST:-${!agent}\}
        done
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after the test ran, it left behide $SHARD_DIRECTORY/arc## directory that need to be cleaned&lt;/p&gt;</description>
